issues.title: Wire x402 payment into headless-markets before nullpath gains traction
issues.reason: Build stall: ~7 days since last build (#38, 2026-02-20). 13th+ consecutive watcher cycle with no new builds. x402 (HTTP 402 Payment Required) is becoming the agent-to-agent payment standard on Base. nullpath.com uses it. headless-markets architecture supports it natively. No issue has been opened to wire it yet — this is the 14th+ cycle this has been flagged. Every cycle without this is compounding risk vs nullpath.
